requirement_issues.requirement_text: The water recycling subsystem shall filter water in accordance with safety water standards defined by regulatory bodies.

issues.description: The term 'safety water standards defined by regulatory bodies' is vague and could refer to multiple standards (EPA, WHO, etc.).
issues.suggested_fix: Specify the exact standards or regulatory citations (e.g., EPA 40 CFR Part 141, WHO Guidelines) to be followed.

issues.description: Elsewhere (REQ-058) the term 'potable water standards' is used with explicit reference to EPA and WHO, creating inconsistent terminology.
issues.suggested_fix: Unify terminology by referring consistently to 'potable water standards' and listing the specific regulatory bodies.

issues.description: No clear criteria or test procedure is provided for verifying compliance with the unspecified standards.
issues.suggested_fix: Define measurable acceptance criteria (e.g., maximum contaminant levels in ppm) and test methods.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The water recycling subsystem shall include a monitoring device that alerts the LSF when the filtering system requires change or maintenance, with data retrieved via a dedicated application.

issues.description: The dedicated application is not defined—no platform, interface, or data model is specified.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify the application platform (mobile, desktop), API interfaces, data formats, and authentication requirements.

issues.description: The requirement does not specify the format or method of the alert.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify how the alert is communicated (e.g., visual, audible, via control system).

issues.description: Domain model lacks an Application class or interface to retrieve monitoring data.
issues.suggested_fix: Introduce an Application class with methods or interfaces to pull data from the MonitoringDevice.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The water storage subsystem shall store potable, black, and gray water for occupants, meeting capacity requirements as defined in the Water Storage Tank SRS.

issues.description: The requirement references an external document without providing the capacity details.
issues.suggested_fix: Include the capacity requirements directly in the requirement or ensure the referenced Water Storage Tank SRS document is accessible.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The water storage subsystem shall include a monitoring device that communicates water quality and contamination levels to the LSF.

issues.description: The requirement does not specify the frequency or method of communication.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify how often and in what format the water quality data is communicated.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Store non-perishable and perishable goods. Non-perishable items shall be stored in a clean, dry environment near the kitchen, while perishable goods require adequate refrigeration/freezing capacity for extended periods.

issues.description: No quantitative parameters for 'clean, dry environment' or 'adequate refrigeration/freezing capacity' are provided.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify acceptable temperature range, humidity level, and storage capacity in cubic feet or cubic meters.

issues.description: The phrase 'near the kitchen' is qualitative; no spatial requirement is defined.
issues.suggested_fix: Define a spatial requirement (e.g., within 5 feet of the kitchen module).

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Monitor the health of critical equipment via a network of wired or wireless sensors covering systems such as power generation, HVAC, water purification, waste management, and drilling.

issues.description: Sensor types, health metrics, reporting intervals, network coverage, and thresholds are unspecified.
issues.suggested_fix: Define equipment health metrics (e.g., temperature, pressure), list sensor types, specify reporting intervals, data thresholds, and network protocols.

issues.description: Domain model lacks a generic EquipmentHealthSensor class for various sensor types.
issues.suggested_fix: Introduce an EquipmentHealthSensor class with attributes for sensorType and connectionType to support different equipment sensors.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Provide sufficient storage and maintenance space for expedition and drilling equipment, including heavy machinery, transport vehicles, and maintenance tools, with appropriate environmental controls.

issues.description: 'Sufficient' storage area and 'appropriate environmental controls' are undefined.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify required floor area/volume, weight capacity, and environmental parameters (e.g., temperature, dust control).

issues.description: No classes represent drilling equipment storage or maintenance workshops.
issues.suggested_fix: Add DrillingEquipmentStorage and MaintenanceSpace classes with capacity and environmental attributes.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Store ice cores. The facility shall be capable of simultaneously storing 20 ice cores at temperatures maintained between -40°F and 20°F.

issues.description: The temperature range conflicts with REQ-042 which states the facility must withstand -40°F to 80°F.
issues.suggested_fix: Align the temperature ranges or clarify the difference between operational and storage requirements.

issues.description: Temperature range is held in a single string; cannot be validated numerically.
issues.suggested_fix: Use separate numeric attributes minTemperature and maxTemperature for enforcement.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Support scientific data exchange with the US research lab through encrypted transmission.

issues.description: No protocols, endpoints, or lab identifiers are specified for the encrypted exchange.
issues.suggested_fix: Define communication protocols (e.g., SFTP, HTTPS), target hostnames, and encryption algorithms.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The LSF shall contain at least three computers to support data transmission, with data storage maintained on an encrypted server.

issues.description: The 'at least three' requirement is not enforced in the CommunicationSystem→Computer relationship multiplicity.
issues.suggested_fix: Constrain targetMultiplicity to 3..* for CommunicationSystem→Computer.

issues.description: The requirement does not specify the role or configuration of the computers.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify whether the computers are for general use, data processing, or specific tasks.

issues.description: Encrypted server is not modeled; unclear where or how data are stored.
issues.suggested_fix: Add an EncryptedServer class with an isEncrypted attribute and link to computers or CommunicationSystem.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The LSF shall be designed for transportability by LC-130 or C-130 Hercules aircraft to McMurdo Station.

issues.description: This requirement conflicts with REQ-020, which mentions transport by helicopter, truck, or sleds.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify whether the facility must be transportable by all methods or if these are alternative options.

issues.description: No weight, dimension, or certification criteria are provided for airlift compatibility.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify maximum dimensions, weight limits, and reference MIL-STD-1366 criteria.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The LSF shall also be designed for transport by helicopter, truck, or sleds pulled by ground vehicles.

issues.description: Ground transport parameters (terrain, attachment points, load distribution) are undefined.
issues.suggested_fix: Define environmental and mechanical requirements for helicopter hooks, truck axles, and sled fixtures.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Provide accommodation with at least five beds and one mobile cot.

issues.description: No acceptance procedure is defined to verify bed and cot counts.
issues.suggested_fix: Define inspection criteria or automated inventory checks for Accommodation.numberOfBeds and numberOfMobileCots.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The facility shall have at least two sinks.

issues.description: Multiplicity for LSF→Sink is 1..*, which does not enforce a minimum of two sinks.
issues.suggested_fix: Change the relationship multiplicity to 2..*.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The facility shall include at least a two-burner table-top stove.

issues.description: Domain model only has a generic Stove; 'table-top' attribute is not captured.
issues.suggested_fix: Add attribute isTableTop: Boolean to Stove or define a TableTopStove subclass.

issues.description: Minimum burner count is not enforced.
issues.suggested_fix: Constrain Stove.burners to be >= 2.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The facility shall conserve energy by utilizing motion sensor switches and outlets.

issues.description: No behavior or coverage area is defined for sensors controlling outlets or switches.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify detection range, control logic, and list which circuits are sensor-driven.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The facility structure shall support a roof load of 60 lbs per square foot for ice/snow buildup.

issues.description: Domain model has no structural element to capture roof load capacity.
issues.suggested_fix: Add attribute roofLoadCapacity: Float to LSF or introduce a Structure class for load ratings.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The facility shall store at least 150 lbs of food per week.

issues.description: No model for food storage capacity by weight over time.
issues.suggested_fix: Introduce a FoodStorage class with attribute weeklyCapacity: Float (lbs).

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The facility shall adhere to the 30-70-20 Pollution Prevention Policy.

issues.description: The requirement does not explain what the 30-70-20 Pollution Prevention Policy entails.
issues.suggested_fix: Provide details or a reference to the policy's specifications.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The facility shall adhere to the 30-50-75 Environmental Effects Abroad of Major Agency Actions.

issues.description: The requirement does not explain what the 30-50-75 policy entails.
issues.suggested_fix: Provide details or a reference to the policy's specifications.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The facility shall remind occupants to replace water and air filters as per the manufacturer's instructions.

issues.description: ControlSystem.remindFilterReplacement is generic; the domain model lacks an AirFilter concept.
issues.suggested_fix: Model an AirFilter class and extend reminder logic to include both water and air filters.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Medical supplies shall be restocked weekly as needed.

issues.description: 'Weekly as needed' is contradictory—no threshold or schedule is defined.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify restocking criteria, for example restock every Monday or when kit count falls below a set number.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Software and firmware updates shall not interrupt critical system functions.

issues.description: The requirement is vague about what constitutes 'interruption' and does not enumerate critical system functions.
issues.suggested_fix: List which functions are critical, specify acceptable downtime or degradation windows, and define fail-over behaviors.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Software and firmware updates shall be executed manually.

issues.description: This requirement conflicts with REQ-075, which specifies that updates should not interrupt critical system functions.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify whether manual updates can be scheduled during non-critical periods or if automated updates are allowed for non-critical systems.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: All control panels shall be locked.

issues.description: No ControlPanel class exists and no locking mechanism or standard is defined.
issues.suggested_fix: Add a ControlPanel class with attribute locked: Boolean and reference applicable locking standards.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Control panels shall be accessible only from within the facility.

issues.description: Undefined boundary for 'within the facility' (physical vs. network).
issues.suggested_fix: Specify access control zones, network segmentation, or geofencing requirements.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The control system shall be operable via a stand-alone smart device (e.g., tablet) or from a dedicated control panel.

issues.description: The requirement does not specify if both methods must be available simultaneously or if they are alternatives.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify whether the system must support both control methods concurrently or if either is sufficient.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The monitoring system shall include a fire-suppression system.

issues.description: Unclear whether the monitoring system controls suppression activation or is simply co-located.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify that MonitoringDevice must trigger the FireSuppressionSystem upon detection of fire events.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The potable water system shall feature a visible display of pH level.

issues.description: Requirement uses the term 'potable water system' but domain model class is WaterRecyclingSubsystem.
issues.suggested_fix: Use consistent terminology or explicitly map 'potable water system' to WaterRecyclingSubsystem.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for the WaterRecyclingSubsystem's 'hasVisiblePHDisplay' attribute to be displayed and monitored
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The water recycling subsystem shall display the pH level visibly and ensure it is monitored continuously.
missing_requirements.rationale: The attribute 'hasVisiblePHDisplay' is present in the domain model but no requirement defines its use or monitoring; continuous pH monitoring is critical for ensuring water quality.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for the WaterStorageSubsystem's 'potableWaterVolume', 'grayWaterVolume', and 'blackWaterVolume' attributes to be monitored, reported, and threshold alerts provided
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The water storage subsystem shall continuously monitor and report the volumes of potable, gray, and black water to the LSF control system and include level sensors that alert occupants when any volume falls below 10% or exceeds 90% of capacity.
missing_requirements.rationale: The domain model includes these volume attributes but lacks requirements for monitoring, reporting, and alerting, which are essential to manage water resources, prevent shortages, and avoid overflows.

missing_requirements.description: No functional requirement for treating and recycling stored gray and black water
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The facility shall include a dedicated gray/black water treatment subsystem that processes stored gray and black water to meet EPA secondary standards and recycles treated water for non-potable uses such as toilet flushing and laundry.
missing_requirements.rationale: Without a treatment subsystem, stored sewage can accumulate, posing health risks and violating environmental protection regulations; recycling treated water optimizes resource use.

missing_requirements.description: Missing specification of power generation capacity, redundancy, and failover times
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The power generation subsystem shall deliver at least 15 kW of continuous power with 30 kWh of battery backup, automatically switch to backup generators or renewable sources within 5 seconds of a primary failure, and log all switchover events.
missing_requirements.rationale: Continuous, redundant power is essential for life-support functions; undefined capacity and failover procedures jeopardize occupant safety and mission-critical operations.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for the DisposalSystem's 'effectiveUnderExtremeWeatherConditions' attribute to be validated and maintained
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The disposal system shall be tested and validated to ensure it remains effective under extreme ambient temperatures as defined in system specifications.
missing_requirements.rationale: The attribute is present in the domain model but lacks validation requirements; confirming disposal effectiveness under harsh conditions is critical for waste management reliability.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for the DisposalSystem to include fault detection and maintenance notifications
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The disposal system shall include sensors to detect blockages, jams, or motor failures and shall alert occupants and the control system within 2 minutes of detecting any fault.
missing_requirements.rationale: Monitoring system health and notifying of faults prevents waste backups and downtime, ensuring continuous operation.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for the IceCoreStorage's 'temperatureRange' attribute to be actively monitored and failure notifications provided
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The ice core storage subsystem shall maintain internal temperatures between -40°F and 20°F, monitor continuously, and alert occupants via the control system if temperatures deviate outside this range for more than 5 minutes.
missing_requirements.rationale: Maintaining and monitoring precise temperature ranges with timely alerts preserves the scientific integrity of ice core samples.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for the Radio's 'batteryBackup', 'handCrankFunction', and 'solarPower' attributes to be tested and maintained
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The radio system shall be tested regularly to ensure the battery backup, hand-crank function, and solar power capabilities are operational, and maintenance actions shall be recorded.
missing_requirements.rationale: These attributes are critical for reliable communication in emergencies, but no requirements exist for their testing, maintenance, and validation.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for the AEDDefibrillator's 'complianceStandard' attribute to be validated and documented
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The AED defibrillator shall be validated and documented to ensure compliance with regulatory standard 29 CFR 1915.87.
missing_requirements.rationale: Regulatory compliance documentation for medical equipment is essential to ensure safety and adherence to standards.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for the FuelStorage's 'complianceStandard' attribute to be validated and documented
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The fuel storage system shall be validated and documented to ensure compliance with EPA SPCC requirements (40 CFR Part 112).
missing_requirements.rationale: Validation and documentation of compliance standards are critical for safety, environmental protection, and regulatory adherence.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for the FuelStorage to include leak and spill detection with automatic isolation
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The fuel storage system shall include leak and spill detection sensors with automatic isolation valves and shall alert the control system within 1 minute of detecting any leak or spill.
missing_requirements.rationale: Early detection and automatic isolation of fuel leaks prevent environmental contamination and reduce fire hazards.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for the ControlSystem's 'passwordProtected' attribute to include role-based access, password complexity, and multi-factor authentication
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The control system shall implement role-based access control with at least two roles (Operator and Administrator), enforce password complexity (minimum 12 characters with mixed case, numbers, and symbols), require regular password updates, and support two-factor authentication for administrative functions.
missing_requirements.rationale: Enhanced authentication and authorization controls are required to prevent unauthorized changes to critical life-support systems.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for automatic activation, testing, and maintenance of the FireSuppressionSystem with occupant alarms
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: Upon fire detection, the fire suppression system shall automatically deploy the extinguishing agent within 10 seconds, activate audible alarms and visual evacuation indicators facility-wide, and be tested and maintained regularly to ensure operational readiness.
missing_requirements.rationale: Automatic suppression, alarms, and regular testing are critical to occupant safety and compliance with fire safety codes.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for an emergency shutdown or safe-mode procedure in the control system
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The control system shall provide an emergency shutdown mode that safely powers down non-essential subsystems, maintains critical life-support functions, and allows authorized personnel to initiate or abort via the password-protected control panel.
missing_requirements.rationale: A controlled shutdown procedure is necessary to protect occupants and equipment during catastrophic failures or evacuations.

missing_requirements.description: Missing HVAC and indoor air quality requirements
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The facility HVAC system shall maintain indoor temperatures between 68°F and 75°F, relative humidity between 30% and 50%, filter particulates down to 0.3 microns with HEPA filters, monitor CO2 levels, and alert occupants if thresholds are exceeded.
missing_requirements.rationale: Proper climate control and air quality safeguards are essential for occupant health, comfort, and safety in extreme environments.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for audit logging of control actions and sensor events
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The control system shall log all user commands (from control panel or remote interfaces), automated sensor alerts, and system events with timestamps and user IDs, retaining logs for at least 90 days in the facility database.
missing_requirements.rationale: Audit logs are essential for troubleshooting, incident investigation, and regulatory compliance.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for data and configuration backup and recovery mechanisms
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: All critical data (sensor logs, configuration files, scientific data) and system configurations shall be backed up daily to remote cloud storage, with backups retained for at least 30 days and support for point-in-time restoration.
missing_requirements.rationale: Regular backups and recovery procedures are necessary to prevent data loss and enable rapid recovery after failures.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for the RefrigerationSystem's 'refrigerationSpace' and 'freezerSpace' attributes, temperature control, and alarm thresholds
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The refrigeration subsystem shall continuously monitor and report available refrigeration and freezer space to ensure required capacities, maintain temperatures between 34°F and 40°F for refrigerated goods and -4°F and 0°F for freezer goods, and alert occupants if temperatures deviate by more than ±2°F for over 10 minutes.
missing_requirements.rationale: Monitoring space, enforcing temperature bands, and providing alarms prevent spoilage of perishable supplies.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for MotionSensor integration with energy conservation and timeout behavior
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: Motion sensors shall be integrated with lighting and other energy-consuming systems to detect occupancy and automatically deactivate associated devices after 5 minutes of no detected motion to conserve energy.
missing_requirements.rationale: Defined timeout behavior and integration with energy systems ensure consistent energy savings when areas are unoccupied.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for the Network's 'wifiSpeed' attribute to be monitored and reported
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The network subsystem shall continuously monitor and report Wi-Fi speed to ensure it meets a minimum requirement of 25 Mbps and alert the control system if speeds drop below this threshold.
missing_requirements.rationale: Monitoring network performance is essential to ensure data communications meet operational requirements.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for the StorageEnvironment's 'locationDescription' attribute to be documented and accessible
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The storage environment's location description shall be documented and made accessible to all occupants via the facility information system.
missing_requirements.rationale: Documenting and sharing location descriptions aids logistics, orientation, and emergency response.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for the Furniture's 'tables' and 'chairs' attributes to be maintained and inventoried
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The furniture inventory shall be maintained and reported regularly to ensure all tables and chairs are in good condition and available for use.
missing_requirements.rationale: Maintaining and tracking furniture condition and availability supports occupant comfort and facility planning.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for the Stove's 'burners' attribute to be tested and maintained
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The stove shall be tested and maintained regularly to ensure all burners are operational and safe for use.
missing_requirements.rationale: Regular testing and maintenance of burners are critical for safety and functionality in food preparation.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for emergency lighting during power failures
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: Emergency lighting circuits shall provide at least 1 foot-candle of illumination in all corridors, exit routes, and critical areas for a minimum of 90 minutes upon loss of primary power, powered by dedicated battery backup.
missing_requirements.rationale: Emergency illumination is crucial for safe evacuation and operations during power outages.

domain_model_issues.description: The MonitoringDevice class does not include attributes for the metrics it monitors (waterQualityLevel, filterStatus, contaminationLevels, lastMaintenanceDate).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add attributes 'waterQualityLevel': Float, 'filterStatus': String, 'contaminationLevels': Float, and 'lastMaintenanceDate': Date.

domain_model_issues.description: No class models the dedicated application for retrieving maintenance data from MonitoringDevice.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add an Application class with interfaces to MonitoringDevice and data-pull methods.

domain_model_issues.description: The WaterRecyclingSubsystem class does not include attributes for the dedicated monitoring application.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add an attribute 'monitoringAppDetails': String or detailed type.

domain_model_issues.description: The ControlSystem class does not include attributes for smart device compatibility and control panel details.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add attributes 'smartDeviceCompatibility': String or Boolean and 'controlPanelLockStatus': Boolean.

domain_model_issues.description: The remindFilterReplacement method covers generic filters only; the air filtration subsystem and water filters are not modeled separately.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Define an AirFilter class and extend remindFilterReplacement to handle separate filter types.

domain_model_issues.description: No SmartDevice class for operating the ControlSystem via tablet or mobile devices.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add SmartDevice class with attributes 'deviceType': String and 'connectivity': String.

domain_model_issues.description: No ControlPanel class exists for locking and access control of the ControlSystem.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Introduce ControlPanel class with attributes 'locked': Boolean and 'accessZone': String.

domain_model_issues.description: The FireSuppressionSystem class lacks attributes for operational status and suppression method.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add attributes 'isActive': Boolean and 'suppressionMethod': String.

domain_model_issues.description: The relationship is currently an association but should be a composition since the FireSuppressionSystem is part of the LSF.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Change the relationship type to composition.

domain_model_issues.description: No relationship allows the MonitoringDevice to trigger the FireSuppressionSystem automatically on detection.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add an association so MonitoringDevice can activate FireSuppressionSystem on alarms.

domain_model_issues.description: The LSF class does not include attributes for transportability requirements such as weight and dimensions.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add attributes 'transportWeight': Float and 'transportDimensions': String.

domain_model_issues.description: No attribute captures roof load capacity for snow and ice buildup.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add 'roofLoadCapacity': Float attribute to LSF.

domain_model_issues.description: Transport modes (aircraft, helicopter, truck, sled) and standards (e.g., MIL-STD-1366) are not modeled.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Introduce TransportabilityCriteria class with 'allowableModes': List<String> and 'standardReferences': List<String>.

domain_model_issues.description: Multiplicity is 1..* but REQ-024 requires at least 2 sinks.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Update the relationship to targetMultiplicity 2..*.

domain_model_issues.description: Stored as a single String; cannot enforce numeric min/max temperature values.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Replace with separate 'minTemperature': Float and 'maxTemperature': Float attributes.

domain_model_issues.description: Lacks a generic sensor class for health monitoring of critical equipment.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Introduce EquipmentHealthSensor with attributes 'sensorType': String and 'connectionType': String.

domain_model_issues.description: No class represents storage for drilling equipment or replacement hardware.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add DrillingEquipmentStorage class with attributes 'capacity': Float and 'replacementHardware': List<String>.

domain_model_issues.description: Multiplicity is 1..* but REQ-016 requires at least 3 computers.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Change targetMultiplicity to 3..*.

domain_model_issues.description: No representation of the encrypted server for secure data storage.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add EncryptedServer class with 'isEncrypted': Boolean and a relationship to CommunicationSystem.

domain_model_issues.description: The MotionSensor class lacks methods and attributes to control power outlets and network reporting.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add methods 'detectMotion()' and 'switchPower()', and attribute 'connectionType': String.

domain_model_issues.description: No model for weekly food storage capacity by weight.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Introduce FoodStorage class with attribute 'weeklyCapacity': Float.

domain_model_issues.description: Environmental and regulatory policies (e.g., Antarctic Treaty, OSHA, IBC) are not represented.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add CompliancePolicy class with 'policyName': String and 'referenceDetails': String.

domain_model_issues.description: No class models software and firmware update execution or scheduling.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add SoftwareUpdateManager class with attributes 'updateMode': String and 'interruptionProtection': Boolean.

domain_model_issues.description: No mechanism captures weekly restocking schedules for the first aid kit.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add 'restockFrequency': Integer or String attribute to FirstAidKit.

domain_model_issues.description: The class name is misspelled as 'Accommodation' in the model.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Correct the class name to 'Accommodation'.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The water recycling subsystem shall filter water in accordance with safety water standards defined by regulatory bodies.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: REQ-002 (Version 1.0, Draft, Priority: High; Actor: WaterRecyclingSubsystem): The system shall filter raw water to meet EPA and WHO potable water safety standards as referenced in Water Subsystem SRS (REQ-058). Source: Water Subsystem SRS. Acceptance Criteria: Weekly water quality tests demonstrate turbidity <5 NTU and zero contamination, with monthly test reports confirming compliance. Dependencies: REQ-058. Quality Attributes: Safety, Reliability.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Including priority, actor, rationale, source, status, version, dependencies, acceptance criteria, and quality attributes ensures clarity, traceability, and testability by specifying responsible subsystem, referencing standards, and defining measurable criteria.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The water recycling subsystem shall include a monitoring device that alerts the LSF when the filtering system requires change or maintenance, with data retrieved via a dedicated application.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: REQ-003 (Version 1.0, Draft, Priority: Medium): The WaterRecyclingSubsystem shall integrate a MonitoringDevice (as described in the MonitoringDevice class) that detects filter maintenance needs and alerts the LSF ControlSystem within one minute of threshold breach. Maintenance data, including filter lifespan status and contamination levels, shall be transmitted via a password-protected web and mobile application. Source: Water Subsystem SRS. Acceptance Criteria: Alerts generated within 60 seconds of threshold breach; maintenance data accessible in the application. Dependencies: REQ-002. Quality Attributes: Usability, Responsiveness.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Defining priority, rationale, source, status, version, acceptance criteria, dependencies, and quality attributes ensures the requirement is actionable and testable. Specifying device class, alert timing, interface, and security mechanisms clarifies implementation and testing.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The water storage subsystem shall store potable, black, and gray water for occupants, meeting capacity requirements as defined in the Water Storage Tank SRS.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: REQ-004 (Version 2.1, Draft, Priority: High; Actor: WaterStorageSubsystem): Store a minimum of 500 gallons of potable, 300 gallons of gray, and 200 gallons of black water (per Water Storage Tank SRS v2.1) to support five occupants for 14 days. Source: Water Storage Tank SRS v2.1. Acceptance Criteria: Tank volumes for each water type are verified in SRS tests and monitored by the WaterStorageSubsystem class. Dependencies: REQ-002. Quality Attributes: Capacity, Reliability.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Including priority, actor, source version, acceptance criteria, dependencies, and quality attributes ensures verifiable capacity targets, traceability, and operational support over a defined duration.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The water storage subsystem shall include a monitoring device that communicates water quality and contamination levels to the LSF.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: REQ-005 (Version 1.0, Draft, Priority: Medium): The WaterStorageSubsystem shall integrate a MonitoringDevice that measures pH, turbidity, and microbial contamination levels and transmits data to the LSF dashboard every hour via the ControlSystem. Alerts shall trigger if any value exceeds EPA thresholds (REQ-058). Source: Water Storage Tank SRS. Acceptance Criteria: Data delivered hourly with <1 minute latency; contamination alerts issued per thresholds; error rate <5%. Dependencies: REQ-004. Quality Attributes: Accuracy, Timeliness.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Specifying priority, rationale, source, status, version, acceptance criteria, dependencies, and quality attributes, along with measurable parameters and alert conditions, ensures traceability and testability.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Process waste. The facility shall implement a disposal system for trash and waste that remains effective under extreme weather conditions.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: REQ-006 (Version 1.0, Draft, Priority: High; Actor: DisposalSystem): The DisposalSystem shall process up to 50 lbs/day of mixed waste (organic, plastic, hazardous) while maintaining ≥95% throughput in temperatures from -40°F to 80°F (per REQ-042). Weekly waste compaction shall comply with EPA 40 CFR Part 112. Source: LSF Waste Management SRS. Acceptance Criteria: ≥95% throughput confirmed in environmental chamber tests; weekly compaction reports. Dependencies: None. Quality Attributes: Robustness, Reliability.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Adding priority, actor, rationale, source, status, version, acceptance criteria, dependencies, and quality attributes, as well as quantifiable capacity and regulatory references, ensures clear, testable, and traceable requirements.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Store non-perishable and perishable goods. Non-perishable items shall be stored in a clean, dry environment near the kitchen, while perishable goods require adequate refrigeration/freezing capacity for extended periods.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: REQ-007 (Version 1.0, Draft, Priority: Medium; Actor: StorageEnvironment): Provide ≥100 ft³ of dry storage (humidity <30%) adjacent to the kitchen/DiningSpace for non-perishables, and RefrigerationSystem capacity of ≥48 ft³ maintaining 35–40 °F refrigeration for up to 90 days and FreezerSystem capacity of ≥20 ft³ maintaining ≤0 °F freezing for up to 90 days. Source: Food Storage SRS (REQ-034, REQ-035). Acceptance Criteria: Environmental chamber tests confirm <30% humidity in dry storage and stable temperatures over 90-day test. Dependencies: REQ-034, REQ-035. Quality Attributes: Environmental Control, Safety.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Specifying priority, actor, rationale, source, status, version, acceptance criteria, dependencies, and quality attributes, along with quantifiable storage metrics and durations, ensures traceability and testability for food preservation.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Monitor the health of critical equipment via a network of wired or wireless sensors covering systems such as power generation, HVAC, water purification, waste management, and drilling.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: REQ-009 (Version 1.0, Draft, Priority: High; Actor: ControlSystem): Deploy IP67-rated wired/wireless sensors on power generation, HVAC, water purification, waste management, and drilling systems (per REQ-067 through REQ-073) to monitor health metrics. Sensors shall report status every 5 minutes and trigger alerts within 1 minute of fault detection (per REQ-062 to REQ-066). Source: LSF Monitoring SRS. Acceptance Criteria: ≥99% sensor network uptime; alerts delivered within 1 minute; reporting interval maintained. Dependencies: REQ-062, REQ-067. Quality Attributes: Availability, Responsiveness.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Including priority, actor, rationale, source, status, version, acceptance criteria, dependencies, and quality attributes, along with sensor ratings, intervals, and alert thresholds, ensures comprehensive, traceable, and testable monitoring requirements.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Provide sufficient storage and maintenance space for expedition and drilling equipment, including heavy machinery, transport vehicles, and maintenance tools, with appropriate environmental controls.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: REQ-010 (Version 1.0, Draft, Priority: Medium; Actor: StorageEnvironment): Allocate a minimum of 500 ft² of dedicated workshop and storage space for expedition and drilling equipment (per REQ-081), including heavy machinery, transport vehicles, and maintenance tools. Environmental controls shall maintain temperatures between -40 °F and 80 °F with humidity matching ambient conditions (REQ-042). Include lockable tool racks and parts inventory storage per MIL-STD-1366. Source: Drilling Equipment SRS. Acceptance Criteria: Space accommodates specified equipment dimensions; environmental conditions maintained during 7-day tests; lockable racks installed. Dependencies: REQ-019, REQ-081. Quality Attributes: Usability, Environmental Control.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Adding priority, actor, rationale, source, status, version, acceptance criteria, dependencies, and quality attributes, plus clear area size, environmental range, and security features, ensures the requirement is measurable, traceable, and testable.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Store ice cores. The facility shall be capable of simultaneously storing 20 ice cores at temperatures maintained between -40 °F and 20 °F.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: REQ-011 (Version 1.0, Draft, Priority: High): The IceCoreStorage subsystem shall store 20 ice cores (max 6\" diameter x 3 m length) at -40 °F to 20 °F with ±2 °F stability. Temperature shall be logged hourly, with alerts triggered for deviations >5 °F (per NSF Antarctic Specimen Guidelines). Source: Ice Core Handling SRS. Acceptance Criteria: Temperature maintained within tolerance for 48 hours in an environmental chamber; hourly logs and deviation alerts generated. Dependencies: REQ-020. Quality Attributes: Precision, Stability.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Including priority, rationale, source, status, version, dependencies, acceptance criteria, and quality attributes, plus core dimensions and monitoring protocols, ensures verifiability and integrity of specimens.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Support scientific data exchange with the US research lab through encrypted transmission.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: REQ-013 (Version 1.0, Draft, Priority: High): The CommunicationSystem shall encrypt all scientific data transmissions to the US research lab using AES-256 over satellite links supporting at least 12 Mbps download and 3 Mbps upload (per REQ-045/046). RF emissions shall comply with 47 CFR §15.407. Source: Communication SRS. Acceptance Criteria: Encrypted data transfers sustain required throughput without packet loss over a 24-hour test and pass RF emissions compliance. Dependencies: REQ-045, REQ-046, REQ-047. Quality Attributes: Security, Throughput.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Adding priority, rationale, source, status, version, dependencies, acceptance criteria, and quality attributes, along with encryption standards, data rates, and regulatory compliance, ensures the requirement is clear, traceable, and testable.

reasoning.domain_model: Combined classes and relationships from both source models by selecting the most detailed attributes and methods, resolving duplicates by unifying similar concepts (e.g., merging SafetyWaterStandard into boolean compliance flags), and integrating communication and control subsystems under unified classes. Redundant or overlapping classes (e.g., Storage vs. StorageEnvironment) were consolidated. Composition and aggregation relationships reflect containment hierarchies and resource usage. PlantUML diagram was updated to represent the consolidated domain structure.
reasoning.analysis:
Analysis aggregated using openai with specialized component processing:
- requirement_completeness: We merged the deepseek and openai assessments by selecting the minimum completeness_score for each requirement, uniting all missing_elements, and preserving the full suggested_improvement and rationale entries. Since both sources provided identical insights for these requirements, the final values reflect a conservative, comprehensive consolidation of their analyses.
- requirement_issues: Combined issues from both sources per requirement, mapped Ambiguity, Missing Context, Testability, and Implementation to the 'Missing' category, retained Conflict and Inconsistency types, merged similar observations by selecting the highest severity and most detailed descriptions and fixes, aggregated affected model elements, and preserved all unique issues.
- missing_requirements: Both source analyses (deepseek and openai) provided an identical set of 24 missing requirements. To combine them, duplicates were unified without loss of detail. Each requirement retains the most detailed description, category, severity, suggested text, affected model elements, and rationale, and IDs MR1 through MR24 were preserved.
- domain_model_issues: Combined overlapping issues by merging attribute omissions for MonitoringDevice into one comprehensive issue and splitting LSF attribute gaps to preserve severity distinctions. Retained unique missing class, attribute, method, and relationship issues from both sources, mapped 'Incorrect' issue types to 'Inconsistent', and ensured each entry includes clear descriptions and suggested fixes aligned to its affected requirements.
